latestIgtvVideos.title: Curly Hair Routine and Finger Coiling Curly Hair/ No Heat Spiral Curls 💁♥️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
*Earphones Recommend*
(This is my first time doing a voice over, please don't judge and concentrate on the method rather than the voice 😂)
 . 
Hello, I'm here with the video, as requested by everyone!
.
The shampoo that I use is from @wowskinscienceindia it is their "Apple Cider Vinegar shampoo with no Sulphates and Parabens" and the conditioner is "WOW Coconut and Avocado Oil Hair conditioner". 
.
These products changed my hair game, I've been using them since November 2019 and my hair quality has improved like anything.
.
For the shampoo, I take a generous amount and apply it only on my scalp, because that is what need the actual cleaning.
.
I do not use any hair gel/leave in conditioner/setting cream right now ( I may try something in the future). I use this hair conditioner as a leave-in conditioner, i.e., I don't wash off the conditioner, so that my hair doesn't lose it's moisture. 
.
As this product is free of any harmful content, it is absolutely safe to leave it in your hair.
.
I detangle my hair right after conditioning with a wide tooth comb, very lightly. 
.
NOTE: For your hair to look like this, and your curls to be completely trained, you need to practice this routine for a long time. Days, weeks, months, it can take longer than that! Be patient. Also, this works for curly hair and not for straight hair. 🤭
.
Having curly hair is never easy especially because you are surrounded by boys and girls with silky straight hair, making you feel even more insecure about yourself.
.
Even I've been bullied back in the school by many people who called me names just because my hair was different than the other girls. 
.
No one told me how to keep my curly hair because no one around knew about it. It was in college that I started keep my hair as it is after hair wash but that was really difficult and they'd become frizzy the other day. 
.
So, I discovered this routine on YouTube and watched many videos for an affordable option.
.
Hope I could've helped you and you may DM/comment for any queries after watching the video. 💜
.
Be confident in your skin, however you are,don't try to change yourself for others. ♥️ Self love is very important
